{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Poison|type2=Water}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Poison|prevnum=746|prev=Wishiwashi|nextnum=748|next=Toxapex|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Mareanie}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Mareanie\n|jname=ヒドイデ\n|tmname=Hidoide\n|ndex=747\n|type1=Poison\n|type2=Water\n|category=Brutal Star\n|height-ftin=1\'04"\n|height-m=0.4\n|weight-lbs=17.6\n|weight-kg=8.0\n|adex=113\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Merciless\n|ability2=Limber\n|abilityd=Regenerator\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Water 1\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|expyield=61\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=190\n|body=05\n|pokefordex=mareanie\n|generation=7\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Mareanie\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ヒドイデ\'\'\' \'\'Hidoide\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Poison|Water}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VII]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Toxapex}} starting at [[level]] 38.\n\n==Biology==\nMareanie has a purple, stalk-like body and head. It has blue eyes with yellow pupils and sclerae, and three pointed teeth. The body consists of two sections; the top section is slightly smaller and overlaps the lower. On top of its head is a starfish-like collection of ten tentacles. All of the tentacles reach the ground, except for the one directly in front, which is shorter and leaves its face exposed. The tentacles are light blue and covered in purple spines. On top of its head is a purple area with a collection of spikes with a larger, yellow spine in the center. Mareanie is able to regenerate any body part overnight, except its head.\n\n{{p|Bruxish}} feeds on Mareanie, which in turn eats the branches of {{p|Corsola}}. It uses the spike on top of its head to poison its prey and uses its tentacles to either trap its prey or deal the final blow. In the [[SM012|anime]], it has also been seen attaching itself with all of its tentacles and releasing poison through its spines.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:James Mareanie.png|thumb|left|250px|Mareanie in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[James\'s Mareanie]]====\nA female Mareanie debuted in \'\'[[SM012|The Sun, the Scare, the Secret Lair!]]\'\', where she was {{pkmn2|caught}} by [[James]]. She has a very strong affection for James.\n\n====Other====\n[[File:Alternately Colored Mareanie.png|thumb|250px|Differently colored Mareanie in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\nA [[List of alternately colored Pokémon in the anime|differently colored]] Mareanie appeared in \'\'[[SM058|Fighting Back the Tears!]]\'\', where he evolved into a {{p|Toxapex}}. He used to have a crush on James\'s Mareanie. This one has purple tentacles, and green irises, which gives it a slight resemblance to James.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nMultiple Mareanie debuted in \'\'[[SM012|The Sun, the Scare, the Secret Lair!]]\'\', where they scared off a group of {{p|Corsola}} that {{Ash}} was hoping to catch. {{an|Kiawe}} warned Ash that they were dangerous, causing them to flee.\n{{-}}\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Alola}}\n{{Animedexbody|SM012|Mareanie|Rotom Pokédex|Mareanie, the Brutal Star Pokémon. A {{t|Poison}} and {{t|Water}} type. Their head spikes are poisonous and when they attack, they turn upside down and trap prey with their 10 legs.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Sun & Moon\'\'|Alola}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Moon Mareanie Adventures.png|thumb|right|170px|Mareanie in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nMareanie debuts in \'\'[[PASM06|The Party Crasher and Guzma the Destroyer]]\'\', where one appears under the ownership of {{adv|Moon}}.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Mareanie (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Poison|type2=Water}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VII}}\n{{Dex/Gen/3|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|num1=113|label1={{gameabbrev7|SM}}:|reg2=Alola|num2=136|label2={{gameabbrev7|USUM}}:|reg3=Kanto}