{{Spritebox/7|ndex=747}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|747|Mareanie}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Mareanie\'s evolution into Toxapex also has the greatest {{wp|standard deviation}} of all Pokémon, with 45.72, meaning that the changes to its base stats on evolving are the most uneven of all Pokémon.\n* When encountered in an [[SOS Battle]] as an ally called by {{p|Corsola}}, it will attack the {{pkmn2|wild}} Corsola instead of attacking the player\'s Pokémon.\n\n===Origin===\nMareanie appears to be based on a {{wp|crown-of-thorns starfish}}, a venomous starfish which preys on coral polyps (similar to how Mareanie preys on Corsola).\n\n====Name origin====\nMareanie may be a combination of \'\'marine\'\' and \'\'meanie\'\'.\n\nHidoide may be a combination of 酷い \'\'hidoi\'\' (cruel) and 海星 \'\'hitode\'\' (sea star).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Poison|type2=Water\n|ja=ヒドイデ \'\'Hidoide\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|酷い \'\'hidoi\'\'|cruel}} and {{tt|海星 \'\'hitode\'\'|sea star}}\n|fr=Vorastérie|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|vorace|voracious}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|astérie|sea star}}\'\'\n|es=Mareanie|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Garstella|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|garstig|nasty}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|stella marina|Latin for sea star}}\'\'\n|it=Mareanie|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=시마사리 \'\'Simasari\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|심하다 \'\'simhada\'\'|severe}} and {{tt|불가사리 \'\'bulgasari\'\'|sea star}}\n|zh_cmn=好壞星 / 好坏星 \'\'Hǎohuàixīng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|好壞 / 好坏 \'\'hǎohuài\'\'|very bad}} and {{tt|海星 \'\'hǎixīng\'\'|sea star}}\n|zh_yue=好壞星 \'\'Hóuwaaihsīng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|好壞 \'\'hóuwaaih\'\'|very bad}} and {{tt|海星 \'\'hóisīng\'\'|sea star}}\n|ru=Марини \'\'Marini\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[James\'s Mareanie]]\n<!--\n==Notes==\n<references/>-->\n\n==External links==\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Poison|type2=Water}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Poison|prevnum=746|prev=Wishiwashi|nextnum=748|next=Toxapex}}\n|}\n{